    "# Recurrent Neural Network Applications"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ec3b85c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "But, how many layers and past time steps of data should we use?  Depends on the problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "Is there a way we can let the network figure this out?\n",
    "\n",
    "YES!  If we require the first three layers to share the same weights and convert the delayed lines into feedback, or recurrent connections, we end up with a recurrent neural network!\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "Phew!   Okay.   Now to code it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's just extend our classes from [neuralnetworksA4.py.txt](https://www.cs.colostate.edu/~anderson/cs545/notebooks/neuralnetworksA4.py.txt)"

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import neuralnetworksA4 as nn\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 237,
   "id": "54af2809",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2022-11-17T17:06:58.337186Z",
     "start_time": "2022-11-17T17:06:58.327096Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# X is (n_sequences, sequence_length, D)    Can be overlapping windows.\n",
    "# T is (n_sequences, sequence_length, K)    K is number of outputs\n",
    "\n",
    "class NeuralNetworkRNN(nn.NeuralNetwork):\n",
    "    \"\"\"One recurrent layer, followed by an output layer.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __init__(self, n_inputs, n_hiddens, n_outputs):\n",
    "\n",
    "        if len(n_hiddens) != 1:\n",
    "            raise Exception('NeuralNetworkClassifierRNN: second argument must be list with one integer.')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Change n_inputs to include n_hiddens for each recurrent connection\n",
    "        super().__init__(n_inputs + n_hiddens[0], n_hiddens, n_outputs)\n",
    "        self.n_hiddens = n_hiddens[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _forward(self, X):\n",
    "        \"\"\"X.shape is (N, S, D), where N is number of samples, S is steps in sequence, D is dim of input.\"\"\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        N, S, D = X.shape\n",
    "        H = self.n_hiddens\n",
    "\n",
    "        X1 = self._add_ones(X)\n",
    "        Z = np.zeros((N, S, H))\n",
    "        for s in range(S):\n",
    "            if s == 0:\n",
    "                Z[:, s, :] = np.tanh( X1[:, s, :] @ self.Ws[0][:D + 1, :] )\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                Z[:, s, :] = np.tanh( np.hstack((X1[:, s, :], Z[:, s - 1, :]))  @ self.Ws[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "        Y = self._add_ones(Z) @ self.Ws[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "        self.Zs = [X, Z, Y]\n",
    "        return self.Zs\n",
    "       \n",
    "    def _error_f(self, X, T):\n",
    "        Zs = self._forward(X)\n",
    "        mean_sq_error = np.mean((T - Zs[-1][:, -1, :]) ** 2)\n",
    "        return mean_sq_error\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _gradient_f(self, X, T):\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Assumes _forward just called with layer outputs saved in self.Zs.\n",
    "        n_samples = X.shape[0]\n",
    "        n_outputs = T.shape[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # only calculate errors for Y at end of each sequence\n",
    "        Y = self.Zs[-1][:, -1, :]\n",
    "        delta = -(T - Y) / (n_samples * n_outputs)\n",
    "        self._backpropagate(delta)\n",
    "        return self.all_gradients\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _backpropagate(self, delta):\n",
    "        # delta is (N, S, K)\n",
    "        X1 = self._add_ones(self.Zs[0])\n",
    "        Z = self.Zs[1]\n",
    "        N, S, H = Z.shape\n",
    "       \n",
    "        self.Grads[1][:] = self._add_ones(Z[:, -1, :]).T @ delta\n",
    "        self.Grads[0][:] = 0\n",
    "        delta = delta @ self.Ws[1][1:, :].T * (1 - Z[:, -1, :] ** 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "        n_inputs_X = self.Zs[0].shape[2]\n",
    "        for s in range(S - 1, -1, -1):\n",
    "            self.Grads[0][:] += np.hstack((X1[:, s - 1, :], Z[:, s - 1, :])).T @ delta\n",
    "            delta = delta @ self.Ws[0][n_inputs_X + 1:, :].T * (1 - Z[:, s-1, :] ** 2)\n",
    "            \n",
    "        self.Grads[0][:] /= S"
   ]

   "source": [
    "That class is for regression problems.  Here is a version for classification problems."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 238,
   "id": "4ebbb40a",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2022-11-17T17:06:59.801808Z",
     "start_time": "2022-11-17T17:06:59.791555Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if True:\n",
    "    activation_f = np.tanh\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    activation_f = lambda s: np.where(s > 0, s, 0.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class NeuralNetworkClassifierRNN(nn.NeuralNetworkClassifier):\n",
    "    \"\"\"One recurrent layer, followed by an output layer.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __init__(self, n_inputs, n_hiddens, n_outputs):\n",
    "\n",
    "        if len(n_hiddens) != 1:\n",
    "            raise Exception('NeuralNetworkClassifierRNN: second argument must be list with one integer.')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Change n_inputs to include n_hiddens for each recurrent connection\n",
    "        super().__init__(n_inputs + n_hiddens[0], n_hiddens, n_outputs)\n",
    "        self.n_hiddens = n_hiddens[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _forward(self, X):\n",
    "        \"\"\"X.shape is (N, S, D), where N is number of samples, S is steps in sequence, D is dim of input.\"\"\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        N, S, D = X.shape\n",
    "        H = self.n_hiddens\n",
    "\n",
    "        X1 = self._add_ones(X)\n",
    "        Z = np.zeros((N, S, H))\n",
    "        for s in range(S):\n",
    "            if s == 0:\n",
    "                Z[:, s, :] = activation_f( X1[:, s, :] @ self.Ws[0][:D + 1, :] )\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                Z[:, s, :] = activation_f( np.hstack((X1[:, s, :], Z[:, s - 1, :]))  @ self.Ws[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "        Y = self._add_ones(Z) @ self.Ws[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "        self.Zs = [X, Z, Y]\n",
    "        return self.Zs\n",
    "       \n",
    "    # Function to be minimized by optimizer method, mean squared error\n",
    "    def _neg_log_likelihood_f(self, X, T):\n",
    "        Zs = self._forward(X)\n",
    "        Y_softmax = self._softmax(Zs[-1][:, -1, :])\n",
    "        neg_mean_log_likelihood =  - np.mean(T * np.log(Y_softmax + sys.float_info.epsilon))\n",
    "        return neg_mean_log_likelihood\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _gradient_f(self, X, T):\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Assumes _forward just called with layer outputs saved in self.Zs.\n",
    "        n_samples = X.shape[0]\n",
    "        n_outputs = T.shape[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "        Y = self.Zs[-1][:, -1, :]\n",
    "        # only calculate errors for Y at end of each sequence\n",
    "        delta = -(T - Y) / (n_samples * n_outputs)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Step backwards through the layers to back-propagate the error (delta)\n",
    "        self._backpropagate(delta)\n",
    "\n",
    "        return self.all_gradients\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _backpropagate(self, delta):\n",
    "        # delta is (N, S, K)\n",
    "        X1 = self._add_ones(self.Zs[0])\n",
    "        Z = self.Zs[1]\n",
    "        N, S, H = Z.shape\n",
    "       \n",
    "        self.Grads[1][:] = self._add_ones(Z[:, -1, :]).T @ delta\n",
    "        self.Grads[0][:] = 0\n",
    "        delta = delta @ self.Ws[1][1:, :].T * (1 - Z[:, -1, :] ** 2)\n",
    "        # delta = delta @ self.Ws[1][1:, :].T * np.where(Z[:, -1, :] > 0, 1.0, 0.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "        n_inputs_X = self.Zs[0].shape[2]\n",
    "        for s in range(S - 1, -1, -1):\n",
    "            self.Grads[0][:] += np.hstack((X1[:, s - 1, :], Z[:, s - 1, :])).T @ delta\n",
    "            delta = delta @ self.Ws[0][n_inputs_X + 1:, :].T * (1 - Z[:, s-1, :] ** 2)\n",
    "           \n",
    "        self.Grads[0][:] /= S"

   "source": [
    "To create our data sequences, here is a function to convert $X$ into three dimensional matrix, where second axis is the sequence."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 239,
   "id": "3dbc5afa",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2022-11-17T17:07:00.849899Z",
     "start_time": "2022-11-17T17:07:00.846012Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rolling_windows(X, window, n_shift=1):\n",
    "    '''X: multi-dimensional array, first (sample) dimension will be segmented into windows\n",
    "    window: number of samples per window\n",
    "    n_overlap: number of samples of overlap between consecutive windows\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    array of windows'''\n",
    "\n",
    "    n_samples = X.shape[0]\n",
    "    n_windows = int((n_samples - window + 1) / n_shift)\n",
    "    new_shape = (n_windows, window) + X.shape[1:]\n",
    "    new_strides = (X.strides[0] * n_shift, X.strides[0]) + X.strides[1:] \n",
    "    return np.lib.stride_tricks.as_strided(X, shape=new_shape, strides=new_strides)"
   ]
  },

    "import pickle\n",
    "import gzip\n",
    "\n",
    "with gzip.open('mnist.pkl.gz', 'rb') as f:\n",
    "    train_set, valid_set, test_set = pickle.load(f, encoding='latin1')\n",
    "\n",
    "Xtrain = train_set[0]\n",
    "Ttrain = train_set[1].reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Xval = valid_set[0]\n",
    "Tval = valid_set[1].reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Xtest = test_set[0]\n",
    "Ttest = test_set[1].reshape(-1, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "Xtrain = Xtrain.reshape(-1, 28, 28)\n",
    "Xval = Xval.reshape(-1, 28, 28)\n",
    "Xtest = Xtest.reshape(-1, 28, 28)\n",
    "\n",
    "n_train = 50000\n",
    "Xtrain = Xtrain[:n_train, ...]\n",
    "Ttrain = Ttrain[:n_train]\n",
    "\n",
    "batch_size = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "nnet = NeuralNetworkClassifierRNN(28, [100], 10)\n",
    "nnet.set_classes(np.arange(10))\n",
    "\n",
    "n_reps = 1\n",
    "for rep in range(n_reps):\n",
    "    for first in range(0, n_train, batch_size):\n",
    "        # 100 epochs reached 90 to 91 %\n",
    "        nnet.train(Xtrain[first:first + batch_size], Ttrain[first:first + batch_size], 10, 'adam', 0.001, verbose=False)\n",
    "    print('Repitition', rep, 'out of', n_reps, nnet.get_performance_trace()[-1])"
   ]

    "## Model of Marble Dynamics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4996062a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Dynamics from lecture notes 18."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 280,
   "id": "81913454",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2022-11-17T19:19:09.524921Z",
     "start_time": "2022-11-17T19:19:09.520225Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "valid_actions = (-1, 0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "def initial_state():\n",
    "    return np.array([np.random.uniform(0, 10), \n",
    "                     np.random.uniform(-2.0, 2.0)])\n",
    "\n",
    "def next_state(s, a):\n",
    "    '''[0] is position, s[1] is velocity. a is -1, 0 or 1'''    \n",
    "    s = s.copy()\n",
    "    deltaT = 0.1                           # Euler integration time step\n",
    "    s[0] += deltaT * s[1]                  # Update position\n",
    "    force = a\n",
    "    mass = 0.5\n",
    "    s[1] += deltaT * (force / mass - 0.2 * s[1])  # Update velocity. Includes friction\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Bound next position. If at limits, set velocity to 0.\n",
    "    if s[0] < 0:        \n",
    "        s = [0., 0.] \n",
    "    elif s[0] > 10:\n",
    "        s = [10., 0.]\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return np.array(s)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "n_seqs = 10000\n",
    "n_steps_each_seq = 10\n",
    "X = np.zeros((n_seqs, n_steps_each_seq, 2))\n",
    "T = np.zeros((n_seqs, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "for n in range(n_seqs):\n",
    "    s = initial_state()\n",
    "    for step in range(n_steps_each_seq):\n",
    "        action = np.random.choice(valid_actions)\n",
    "        X[n, step, :] = [s[0], action]\n",
    "        s = next_state(s, action)\n",
    "    T[n, 0] = s[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "X.shape, T.shape"
   ]

    "import matplotlib.patches as pltpa \n",
    "from IPython.display import display, clear_output\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 1.7))\n",
    "\n",
    "def draw_at(ax, x, a, color):\n",
    "    y = 0.5 if color == 'blue' else 0.6\n",
    "    ax.add_patch(pltpa.Circle((x, y), 0.5, color=color))\n",
    "    if a != 0:\n",
    "        plt.arrow(x, y , a * 0.4, 0., head_width=0.1, head_length=0.1,\n",
    "                  color='yellow')\n",
    "    plt.xlim(-1, 11)\n",
    "    plt.ylim(0, 2)\n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    \n",
    "n_steps_per_trial = 20\n",
    "\n",
    "for trial in range(100):\n",
    "    x = np.random.uniform(0, 10)\n",
    "    v = np.random.uniform(-4, 4)\n",
    "    s = [x, v]\n",
    "    a = 1\n",
    "    seq = []\n",
    "    for step in range(n_steps_per_trial):\n",
    "        plt.clf()\n",
    "        x = s[0]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if len(seq) < 10:\n",
    "            seq.append([x, a])\n",
    "            predicted_x = x\n",
    "        \n",
    "        plt.plot([0, 10], [0, 0], lw=3, color='gray')\n",
    "        ax = fig.gca()\n",
    "        #ax.add_patch(pltpa.Rectangle((4, 0), 2, 1, color='pink'))\n",
    "        draw_at(ax, x, a, 'blue')\n",
    "        draw_at(ax, predicted_x, a, 'red')\n",
    "\n",
    "        if step % 10 == 0:\n",
    "            a = - a\n",
    "\n",
    "        if len(seq) == 10:\n",
    "            delta_x = nnet.use(np.array(seq, dtype=np.double)[np.newaxis, ...])\n",
    "            predicted_x = seq[-1][0] + delta_x[-1][0]\n",
    "            seq.append([predicted_x, a])\n",
    "            seq.pop(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "        s = next_state(s, a)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        clear_output(wait=True)\n",
    "        display(fig)\n",
    "    \n",
    "clear_output(wait=True)"
   ]

    "            if key != 'eeg':\n",

    "        eegtrials = element['eeg']\n",

    "        print (('  eeg: {:d} trials, each a matrix with {:d} rows' +\n",

   "source": [
    "Now let’s collect all of the segments from this letter ‘d’ trial. First, find the sample indices where each stimulus starts, collect the displayed letters for each stimulus, and keep track of which stimuli are the target letter."

     "data": {

     "execution_count": 15,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "starts = np.where(np.diff(np.abs(eeg[:, -1])) > 0)[0]\n",
    "stimuli = [chr(int(n)) for n in np.abs(eeg[starts+1, -1])]\n",
    "targetLetter = letterd['protocol'][-1]\n",
    "targetSegments = np.array(stimuli) == targetLetter\n",
    "\n",
    "len(starts), len(stimuli), len(targetSegments)"
   ]
